           2) Combat Forces - B-1 Bomber Operations .............................................................................................................................................. $38,372
           Increases funds for the B-1B aircraft's squadron's operational requirements. This investment supports B-1B squadron's increased
           operational needs resulting from an increase in B-1B flying hours. The increased funding will cover the maintenance, sustainment and
           equipment costs; training range access; and weapon storage facilities across their two main operating bases. The B-1 is a key
           component of the U.S. Air Force's global strike capabilities, requiring robust infrastructure and resources to maintain its readiness and
           effectiveness in executing world-wide missions. These actions ensure the B-1 is strategically positioned to respond to global threats and
           supports a wide range of missions, from conventional strike operations to strategic deterrence.

