3) Nuclear Deterrence Combat Forces - Long Range Stand-Off (LRSO) Operational Beddown............................................................... $22,782
Increase fully funds the Air Force Global Strike Command's (AFGSC) and the Air Force Installation Mission Support Command's
operational expenses for the Air Force's LRSO beddown requirements. This investment sustains the U.S. commitment to maintaining a
robust and modern nuclear enterprise and safeguarding national security. The increased funding will cover renovations and minor
construction contracts. The increase in resources will ensure AFGSC can maintain a credible and effective nuclear deterrence as the
LRSO enters Initial Operational Capability.

OP32:
923 Facility Sustain, Restore Mod By Ct
932 Management and Professional Sup Svs
957 Other Costs-Lands and Structures

(FY 2026 Base: $252,776)

4) Nuclear Deterrence Combat Forces - MH-139 Helicopters .................................................................................................................... $62,300
Increase for MH-139 Helicopters supports the DAF's effort to sustain the nuclear triad by funding the security and support missions that
enable the triad. This increase supports the MH-139 Helicopters platform for day-to-day operational requirements. With the transition
from the UH-1N platform, funding is invested to cover various expenses, including maintenance, fuel management, and training. This
action will ensure the MH-139 platform can meet its operational requirements, such as nuclear surety support and other critical
functions.

