5) Nuclear Deterrence Combat Forces - Remote Visual Assessment (RVA) ............................................................................................. $16,107
Increase funding supports RVA security technology capabilities used for monitoring top-side activity at its various launch facilities. This
technology also supports small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (sUAS) or drones, high-resolution cameras (augments reality and better
depth perception), and remote sensing that can be used for infrastructure, evaluating airfields and support intelligence gathering.

OP32:
923 Facility Sustain, Restore Mod By Ct

(FY 2026 Base: $252,776)

6) Nuclear Deterrence Combat Forces - U.S. Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM) Requirements ....................................................... $29,800
Increase supports USSTRATCOMwith a specific focus on equipment maintenance and the movement of personnel essential to its global
mission. USSTRATCOM oversees strategic deterrence, nuclear operations, global strike, and other critical functions, making the
readiness and mobility of its personnel and equipment vital to national and allied security. Funding will ensure mission-critical equipment
is properly maintained to remain operational and reliable. This will also support transportation and deployment of personnel enabling
rapid response to emerging threats, participation in joint exercises, and coordination with allied forces.

OP32:
308 Travel of Persons
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract

(FY 2026 Base: $252,776)

7) Precision Attack Combat Forces - B-21 Raider Beddown Support ...................................................................................................... $138,893
Increase for the B-21 Raider Beddown supports the DAF’s effort to field next-generation weapon systems by funding the expansion for
B-21 Raider operational beddown requirements to support the ongoing delivery of the new weapon systems, new operating locations
and unit standup. Funding supports beddown requirements such as specialized equipment needs, facility furniture, fixtures, and
equipment buildout, movement and relocation of people and equipment and airlift support. Funding will support beddown at the planned
locations, Ellsworth AFB, South Dakota, Whiteman AFB, Missouri and Dyess AFB, Texas. The increased funding will enable the B-21
Raider to achieve its full potential and successfully support its critical mission objectives.

OP32:
702 AMC SAAM (Fund)
925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $900,726)



