3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................. $19,248
Increase funding and manpower (294 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Combat Enhancement Forces’ Program established
requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support Combat Communications, TACS
communication, Tactical Intelligence Cryptologic and ISR activities, and funds Air Force Special Operations and SOF capabilities.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $266,641; FTE Base: 2,126; 294 FTE)

4) Command and Control - Collaborative Combat Aircraft Operations....................................................................................................... $35,300
Increase for fleet readiness mission of Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA) to support our effort to field next-generation weapon
systems by funding the Mission Design Series (MDS) at Beale Air Force Base, California. This funding provides operational and
maintenance support to ensure the readiness and reliability of the CCA fleet, sustainment activities to keep the aircraft and
associated systems in optimal condition over their lifecycle; required renovations and upgrades to facilities ensuring that
administration, secure spaces, and operational areas meet mission requirements, and furniture, fixtures, and equipment to outfit
these spaces with the necessary tools and infrastructure to accommodate personnel and effective mission operations. Funding is
critical to ensuring the operational success of the CCA mission, which involves integrating advanced unmanned and manned aircraft
to enhance combat effectiveness, situational awareness, and mission flexibility. The CCA program represents a key step in
modernizing air combat capabilities by leveraging autonomous systems to complement traditional aircraft in contested environments.

OP32:
920 Supplies and Equipment (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $594,451)




