5) Command and Control - E-3 Airborne Warning and Control System (AWACS) .................................................................................... $19,852
Increases funds for the E-3 AWACS platform. This investment sustains the E-3's continued operational effectiveness through its
ability to operate outside of contested environments and critical role to Airborne Battle Management, Command and Control, and Air
Moving Target Indication Capabilities. The increased funding supports increased operational needs resulting from an increase in
flying hours and will cover essential, daily operational expenses like personnel training, travel, and equipment maintenance. The
increase in funds allows the E-3 to continue providing vital command and control to support military operations.

OP32:
308 Travel of Persons
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)
932 Management and Professional Sup Svs
935 Training and Leadership Development
987 Other Intra-Government Purchases
989 Other Services

(FY 2026 Base: $623,485)

6) Command and Control - Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)................................................................................................................ $62,828
Increase for JSE supports the DAF's effort to enhance high-end training and readiness by funding a cutting-edge virtual simulation
platform designed to address critical gaps in current weapon testing and training infrastructure. The JSE provides a highly realistic
and adaptable environment for simulating complex combat scenarios, enabling the U.S. military to test and refine advanced weapons
systems, tactics, and operational strategies in ways that are not feasible with traditional methods. This funding will support the
development, expansion, and sustainment of JSE assets and environments, ensuring the system remains capable of meeting
evolving mission requirements. The JSE serves four essential functions: (1) integrated development and testing, allowing seamless
evaluation of new systems in a controlled, simulated environment; (2) tactics development, enabling the creation and refinement of
innovative combat strategies; (3) advanced training, providing warfighters with immersive, high-fidelity training experiences to prepare
for real-world operations; and (4) systems experimentation, facilitating the exploration of emerging technologies and concepts. By
investing in JSE enhancements, the military ensures a more efficient, cost-effective, and comprehensive approach to maintaining
readiness and technological superiority.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance by Contract

(FY 2026 Base: $594,451)




