7) Command and Control - U.S. Air Forces Southern (AFSOUTH) Support .............................................................................................. $49,000
Increase for AFSOUTH supports our effort to support multinational operations by funding it’s mobility and logistical support of its
personnel. This will enhance AFSOUTH’s ability to maintain operational readiness, foster strong partnerships, and promote stability
and security throughout the Western Hemisphere which is essential for executing its mission across Central and South America and
the Caribbean.

OP32:
308 Travel of Persons

(FY 2026 Base: $594,451)

8) ISR Combat Enhancement - Permissive Airborne ISR ........................................................................................................................ $180,652
Increases funds for the Permissive Airborne ISR, enhancing capabilities for Government Owned, Contractor Operated (GOCO) DHC-
8 aircraft for specialized missions which are critical for gathering actionable intelligence in low-threat or permissive environments.
This investment strengthens the Air Force's abilities to conduct persistent surveillance, improve mission planning, and support a wide
range of operations while maintaining a cost-effective approach in less contested environments. The increase funding will cover
operational expenses for ISR platforms such as the MQ-9, ensuring they remain effective in providing high-resolution imagery,
signals intelligence, and other critical data to inform decision-making and operational planning. Permissive Airborne ISR plays a vital
role in monitoring adversary activities and enhancing situational awareness in regions where airspace access is uncontested. These
capabilities involve the use of airborne platforms equipped with advanced sensors and communication systems to collect, process,
and disseminate real-time intelligence.

