3) Readiness Exercises - Combat Air Forces (CAF) Exercises ................................................................................................................ $841,557
Increase for CAF exercises supports the DAF's effort to enhance high-end training and readiness by funding realistic, large-scale,
and technologically advanced training exercises. This funding increase directly enables the "train as we fight" mentality to bolster the
joint force lethality needed for strategic competition with near-peer adversaries. This increase enables the Air Force to forge a more
cohesive fighting force by expanding its exercise program, including Large Force Exercises (LFE), in pursuit of readiness-enhancing
venues and certification events to train alongside joint and allied forces for rapid, large-scale peer conflict. The LFE's will stress
several theaters and Combatant Commands, on a global scope, focused on speed and scale that aligns with the demand faced
during rapidly escalating crises.

