989 Other Services

(FY 2026 Base: $357,421)

4) Readiness Training - Enhanced Training Realism ............................................................................................................................... $122,000
Increase for Enhanced Training Realism supports the DAF's effort to enhance high-end training and readiness by funding advanced
training programs and exercises at Nellis AFB, Nevada the premier training hub for the U.S. Air Force, to ensure pilots and aircrew
develop the skills, tactics, and decision-making abilities needed to operate effectively against advanced, near-peer threats in highly
contested environments. This funding restores a high level of combat realism to its schools, including the U.S. Air Force Weapons
School and large-scale exercises such as Red Flag. Additionally, this supports the development and integration of advanced training
systems, including state-of-the-art simulators, realistic threat emulators, and live, virtual, and constructive training environments.
These enhancements will replicate the tactics, techniques, and technologies employed by near-peer adversaries, providing pilots with
realistic and challenging scenarios that closely mirror modern combat conditions.

OP32:
935 Training and Leadership Development




