                     Force fighter pilot workforce to meet operational demands and improve readiness levels in the face of increasing competitive global
                     landscape. This funds additional basic course graduates from formal training units by hiring additional instructors, expanding training
                     resources, and enhancing simulator and flight training capabilities. Additionally, this increase boosts combat readiness by improving
                     pilot absorption, the process of integrating newly trained pilots into operational units, where they gain the experience and skills
                     necessary to become fully mission-capable. This funding postures the Air Force to sustain its operational tempo, maintain air
