INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_AIRFOR_X_044$$, 2027, $$Air Force$$, $$OM_AIRFOR$$, NULL, NULL, $$DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, Subactivity Group 11D
                                                                        86
                                                                  DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE
                                                                      Fiscal Year (FY) 2027 Budget
                                                                Operation and Maintenance, Air Force
                                                                   Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                               Detail by Subactivity Group: Depot Programmed Equipment Maintenance
                                                                            ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed:
The funding in Subactivity Group 11M is for the Depot Purchased Equipment Maintenance (DPEM) portion of the Weapon System Sustainment (WSS) in the centrally
managed portfolio. This includes all the organic and contract depot level maintenance services for the Air Force and other organizations with Depot Maintenance Inter-
service Support Agreements. The customers determine the requirements and provide obligation authority from each of the components in accordance with regulation
AFMAN 63-143 Centralized Asset Management Procedures.



II. Force Structure Summary:
In this Subactivity Group, DPEM supports the readiness of the Air Force's front line operating weapon systems. These assets, which provide the United States with a
viable deterrent posture, include fighter and bomber aircraft, helicopters, and conventional and strategic missiles such as the Minuteman Intercontinental Ballistic Missile.
Collectively, they provide the United States all the core missions of Air Power to produce the effects of Global Vigilance, Global Reach, and Global Power.

The WSS requirements are developed through the Logistics Requirements Determination Process (LRDP), based on operational needs. The LRDP consists of three basic
phases: (1) develop requirements, (2) review, collaborate and validate requirements, (3) certify, prioritize and publish requirements. The process is managed by the
System Program Managers (SPM) and Program Group Managers (PGM) in the web-based tool named Sustainment Planning, Execution, and Reporting System
(SPERS).

The largest WSS sustainment area (DPEM) has individual commodities with their own tailored sub-process specific to aircraft, engines, missiles, other major end items
and software. The lead Major Commands have the overall responsibility for the category of weapon systems. They provide the capability to the Joint Force based on
current and projected demand for each individual weapon system.




                                                                                                                                     $$, $$1e36b87cf4e5171a92e056f91c38fc3c8319a41e36ff29dd9b4754c90f672e51$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
