                                             Detail by Subactivity Group: Depot Programmed Equipment Maintenance
                                                                          ($ In Thousands)



1) Command and Control - E-3 ................................................................................................................................................................. $232,909
 Increase the software and sustaining engineering requirements for the E-3, to prolong the lifespan of this critical airborne command
and control platform. AWACS provides real-time situational awareness, battle management, and early warning capabilities, enabling
the Air Force to maintain air superiority over the horizon in contested environments. This funding addresses increased costs to
sustainment for depot-level maintenance, software upgrades, and the replacement of aging components to ensure mission readiness
for continued fielding and sustainment of advanced air defense sensors that are critical to the North American Aerospace Defense
Command (NORAD) Homeland Defense Mission. The emergence of new, unconventional airborne threats has intensified the need to
expand sensor coverage and enhance early warning capabilities both domestically and abroad. This investment directly supports the
warfighter and national security by improving the detection and tracking of low, slow, and other asymmetrical threats, which enhances
the common air picture and enables a more effective defense.

OP32:
661 AF Consolidated Sustainment
930 Other Depot Maintenance

(FY 2026 Base: $111,769)

2) Combat Forces - B-1 ............................................................................................................................................................................. $108,521
Increase for B-1 Lancer supports our effort to ensure the continued readiness and effectiveness of this premier 4th generation
bomber, a critical asset in the U.S. strategic arsenal with the largest internal payload of any active fleet. Recent inspections have
revealed accelerated fatigue and stress on critical wing and fuselage components, requiring additional inspections, repairs, and
potentially significant structural modifications. The B-1’s unique ability to penetrate advanced air defenses and deliver precision
strikes across the globe makes it a cornerstone of U.S. power projection and a vital deterrent against adversaries. This funding
supports essential sustainment efforts, addressing these structural concerns while enabling upgrades to critical systems, including
low observation coatings, avionics, and mission systems. These enhancements will preserve the B-1’s survivability and lethality in
contested environments, ensuring it remains capable of meeting evolving threats. This effort in sustainment aligns with the National
Defense Strategy’s emphasis on readiness, modernization, and maintaining a credible strategic deterrent.

OP32:
661 AF Consolidated Sustainment
930 Other Depot Maintenance

(FY 2026 Base: $409,148)




