                                                               Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                           Detail by Subactivity Group: Depot Programmed Equipment Maintenance
                                                                        ($ In Thousands)

3) Nuclear Deterrence Operations - B-2 ................................................................................................................................................... $195,079
Increase for the Spirit – B-2 supports our effort to sustain the nuclear triad by funding the B-2 sustainment. This funding ensures the
sustainment of the nation’s premier long-range, low-observable, deep-penetrating strategic bomber, which supports the warfighter by
enabling the destruction of the most heavily defended and high-value adversary targets. This investment addresses the growing
complexity of maintaining the B-2’s unique low-observable characteristics, which are critical to penetrating advanced adversary
defenses. As the fleet ages and threats evolve from recent operations, the requirement to sustain these capabilities has intensified,
driving increased costs for depot-level maintenance, organic software sustainment, and the replacement of critical reparable
components. The funding supports expanded programmed depot maintenance, accelerates critical aft deck repairs, and enables
faster implementation of warfighter-submitted software change requests. These efforts directly enhance the B-2’s relevance in current
operations to carry to the farthest distance, the heaviest ordinance than any other weapon in the department, all the while remaining
a cornerstone of the U.S. nuclear triad. This investment aligns with the National Defense Strategy by prioritizing readiness to address
high-end threats and hold our enemies at risk.

OP32:
661 AF Consolidated Sustainment
930 Other Depot Maintenance

(FY 2026 Base: $413,723)

4) Nuclear Deterrence Operations - Minuteman III - Intercontinental Ballistic Missile (ICBM) ................................................................ $191,590
Increase for the Minuteman III ICBM ensures the sustainment of the ground-based leg of the nuclear triad, a cornerstone of the
United States' safe, secure, and effective nuclear deterrent. This funding addresses the growing complexity and costs of sustaining
the guidance system to proactively repairing test equipment of 60 stands, in addition to the normal Programmed Depot Maintenance
(PDM), sustaining engineering to mitigate obsolescence, and operational software sustainment. It also addresses the refurbishment
of an increasing number of field returns and funds the critical Integration Support Contract (ISC) to maintain system reliability to deter
the only existential threat to the homeland. By ensuring the constant state of readiness of this vital strategic weapon system, the
funding directly supports national security by providing a survivable, intercontinental nuclear deterrent and aligns with the National
Defense Strategy's emphasis on strategic stability and deterrence.

OP32:
661 AF Consolidated Sustainment
930 Other Depot Maintenance

(FY 2026 Base: $353,340)




