The FY 2027 request for Real Property Maintenance includes $6,100,395 thousand of discretionary and $5,395,743 thousand of mandatory
(reconciliation) for a total of $11,496,138 thousand. The FY 2027 mandatory funds continue efforts from FY2026 to continue the critical investment
in foundational readiness and long-term viability of the U.S. Airforce. This funding directly addresses systemic underinvestment in infrastructure,
which has led to a significant backlog of maintenance and repair requirements that threaten mission assurance, combat readiness, and the quality
of life for Airmen.


The FY 2026 spend plan for Real Property Maintenance includes $2,953,608 thousand of discretionary and $2,785,104 thousand of mandatory
(reconciliation) for a total of $5,738,712 thousand.




