2) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $9,433
Increased funding and manpower (213 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Real Property Maintenance Program established
requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support facilities sustainment of all Air Force
installations and large life-cycle sustainment repair and demolition, restoration, and modernization for all Active Air Force MAJCOMs
and USAFA. This program also includes critical maintenance of runways, utility systems, and facilities necessary to support flying
operations.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $685,673; FTE Base: 7,269; 213 FTE)

3) Facilities Restoration and Modernization .............................................................................................................................................. $120,161
Increase in funding to execute targeted restoration and modernization of failed or failing critical infrastructure, directly improving the
condition, safety, and operational readiness of the Department's facility inventory. This investment ensures Air Force infrastructure is
properly sustained, addressing the most urgent repair needs in alignment with the Infrastructure Investment Action Plan (I2AP) and
DoW's strategic focus on facility sustainment. This is restoring Warrior Ethos by investing in the readiness of our facilities and
improving the quality of life of our Airman and Guardians

OP32:
957 Other Costs-Lands and Structures

(FY 2026 Base: $1,770,417)

4) Facilities Sustainment ............................................................................................................................................................................. $61,780
Increase in funds to bring Facilities Sustainment to 93% funding level of FSM, greater than the 85% required through Consolidated
Budget Review Guidance and in line with the Department's focus on adequately funding sustainment to reduce costly and avoidable
Restoration and Modernization activity in the future, improving the overall condition of the Department's facility inventory.

OP32:
957 Other Costs-Lands and Structures

(FY 2026 Base: $334,816)



