                                                                         122
                                                                   DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE
                                                                     Fiscal Year (FY) 2027 Budget
                                                                 Operation and Maintenance, Air Force
                                                                   Budget Activity: Operating Forces
                                                         Detail by Subactivity Group: Cyberspace Sustainment
                                                                            ($ In Thousands)

I. Description of Operations Financed
The funding in Subactivity 11V covers Cyber Sustainment exclusively, which includes the Contractor Logistics Support (CLS), Sustainment Engineering (SE), and
Technical Orders (TO). CLS includes depot level maintenance, contracted maintenance, operating command organizational maintenance, repair, materiel management,
supply and repair parts management, configuration management, technical data management, training, distribution, failure reporting and analysis. SE is focused on efforts
to review, assess, define, and resolve technical or supportability deficiencies revealed in fielded weapon systems, whereas TO provides up-to-date technical data for
weapons systems operating in the electro-magnetic domain.


II. Force Structure Summary
The funding in this Subactivity Group supports the readiness of the Air Force's cyber weapon systems. These programs include Air Force Cyber Defense, Air Force
Intranet Control, and Distributed Cyber Warfare Operations. Collectively, they provide the United States defensive and offensive capabilities across the ubiquitous electro-
magnetic domain.

The Weapons System Sustainment (WSS) requirements are developed through the Logistics Requirements Determination Process (LRDP) based on operational needs.
The LRDP consists of three basic phases: (1) develop requirements, (2) review, collaborate and validate requirements, (3) certify, prioritize and publish requirements. The
entire process is managed by the System Program Managers (SPM) and Program Group Managers (PGM) in the web-based tool named Sustainment Planning,
Execution, and Reporting System (SPERS).

All four WSS sustainment areas (DPEM, CLS, SE & TO) have individual commodities with their own tailored sub-process specific to major end items and software. The
lead Major Command has the overall responsibility for the category of weapon systems. They provide the capability to the Joint Force based on the current and projected
demand for each individual weapon system.




                                                                                                                                    $$, $$22ad47d6fb8e32622580cdbea3a6bee5fa82dc8303c57852fe471aa695201440$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
