8. Program Increases ................................................................................................................................................................................................................................ $68,577

         a) Annualization of New FY 2026 Program ........................................................................................................................................................................... $68,577

                     1) Cyberspace Superiority - Air Force Cyber Defense................................................................................................................................ $22,774
                     Increase funds for the software requirements provided by CLS and SE to accomplish the generation, projection, and sustainment of
                     the only combat power to bring physical effects from the digital domain. This directly support 21st Century warfighters through secure
                     and reliable conduct of both defensive and offensive cyber operations mission sets across cyberspace to prepare the battlefield, while
                     disrupting enemy planning, reaction and execution. This funding expands configuration management, technical orders production,
                     testing/validation and on-site squadron support on non-kinetic weapon system platforms that provide 24/7/365 monitoring and
                     defense of U.S. Air Force Non-Secure Internet Protocol Router (NIPR)/Secret Internet Protocol Router (SIPR) computers, networks,
                     and communications against hostile attack.

                     OP32:
                     930 Other Depot Maintenance (Non-DWCF)

                     (FY 2026 Base: $159,387)

                     2) Cyberspace Superiority - Air Force Intranet Control ............................................................................................................................... $36,064
                     Increase in funding is critical to the Air Force’s ability to operate, defend, and sustain its networks. Increased funding supports the
                     retirement of legacy NIPR gateways and the installation of Next Generation Gateways (NGG) at 13 key locations, enabling DAF
                     transition to a Zero Trust Architecture (ZTA) in compliance with Executive Order 14028 and the DoW’s 2027 Zero Trust mandate. Key
                     investments include; Splunk to increase capacity from 14TB to 20TB required for monitoring of USAF network traffic, other software
                     solutions like Versa for virtual routers, Cribl for data logging, and the sustainment of Palo Alto firewalls across 150 bases to ensure
                     robust perimeter defenses for the Air Force Network (AFNET). Modernizing cyberspace capabilities improves mission success rates
                     for the Air Force’s ability to deter, detect, and defeat cyber threats from peer competitors, in the most contested domain.

                     OP32:
                     930 Other Depot Maintenance (Non-DWCF)

                     (FY 2026 Base: $62,436)




