2) Global Precision Attack - F-35 .............................................................................................................................................................. $566,918
Increase for the F-35 is driven by increased requirements for Contractor Logistics Support (CLS) Spares and Maintenance intended
to address material pricing updates, increased software requirements to address Flight test Support, additional Engines and Depot
Level Reparable spare parts. As the premier 5th generation stealth fleet, the Air Force cost share of the Joint and Coalition program
is determined by consumption and utilization. The Air Force receives more than 45 aircraft a year into the program, growing the active
fleet by 5-9%, all while employing the current pool of inventory into the current contingencies world-wide. These investments into the
core readiness accounts are essential in maintaining the F-35's technological advantage and ensuring its continued contribution to
global precision attack in accordance with the National Defense Strategy.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance by Contract
930 Other Depot Maintenance (Non-DWCF)

(FY 2026 Base: $1,595,371)

3) Nuclear Deterrence Operations - Minuteman III .................................................................................................................................. $370,712
Increase for the Minuteman III – ICBM supports the DAF’s effort to sustain the nuclear triad by funding sustainment costs for ground-
based leg of the triad. This funding will ensure the sustainment of a cornerstone of the United States' safe, secure, and effective
nuclear deterrent. This funding addresses the growing complexity and costs of sustaining the guidance system to proactively
repairing test equipment of 60 stands, in addition to the normal Programmed Depot Maintenance (PDM), Contract Sustainment
Logistic (CLS) support to mitigate obsolescence, and Technical Orders (TO). It also addresses the refurbishment of an increasing
number of field returns and funds the critical Integration Support Contract (ISC) to maintain system reliability to deter the only
existential threat to the homeland. By ensuring the constant state of readiness of this vital strategic weapon system, the funding
directly supports national security by providing a survivable, intercontinental nuclear deterrent and aligns with the National Defense
Strategy’s emphasis on strategic stability and deterrence.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance by Contract
925 Equipment Purchases
930 Other Depot Maintenance (Non-DWCF)

(FY 2026 Base: $267,476)




