                     1) Combat Air Forces ................................................................................................................................................................................ $299,428
                     The Combat Air Forces (CAF) flying hour program is a fundamental pillar of the National Defense Strategy, essential for realizing
                     integrated deterrence and maintaining a combat-credible force. The program directly generates unrivaled pilot proficiency and combat
                     lethality across our bomber and fighter fleets, ensuring our preparedness to deter aggression and prevail in conflict.

                     Investment in flying hours provides the live-flying training necessary to hone advanced warfighting skills. Fighter crews develop
                     proficiency in offensive counter-air, precision strike, and the suppression of enemy air defenses—capabilities that are critical for
                     addressing the pacing challenge from the PRC and maintaining stability in the Indo-Pacific. Simultaneously, bomber crews maintain
                     readiness for long-range strategic missions, ensuring a credible deterrent against attacks on the United States, our allies, and our
                     partners.

                     Funding for the flying hour program yields benefits across the Joint Force and the defense industrial base. It enables the execution of
                     complex, multi-domain tactics in high-fidelity training environments, a critical component for effective campaigning and building a
                     resilient, integrated force. Concurrently, such funding sustains the defense ecosystem by creating predictable demand for the spares
                     and consumables required for sustained, high-tempo operations and surge capabilities.

                     Ultimately, a fully funded flying hour program produces a more lethal, credible, and resilient force in direct alignment with core NDS
                     priorities. It underpins the capability of our air forces to deliver overwhelming power, thereby guaranteeing the air dominance required
                     to deter adversaries, defeat aggression, and provide the Joint Force with the freedom of action necessary to protect the homeland
                     and our national interests.




