2) Formal Training ..................................................................................................................................................................................... $184,524
The Formal Training Program is the bedrock of airpower readiness, directly supporting the National Defense Strategy's imperatives to
build a resilient Joint Force and enduring advantages. Defined by a "quality of hours" philosophy, every training hour is engineered to
maximize combat skill retention, producing aviators prepared for high-end strategic competition. To meet the strategic goal of
increased pilot production, a critical investment is required to cover the corresponding and escalating costs for fuel, spares, and
consumables associated with a higher operational tempo.

Investment in formal training prioritizes preparation for conflict against a pacing challenge by integrating our most advanced platforms
into the curriculum. Flying missions in the F-35 Lightning II provides unparalleled, real-world experience, allowing new pilots to master
the cognitive demands of sensor fusion, data management, and low-observable tactics. Hands-on experience in a networked, 5th-
generation environment is critical for developing the tactical acumen required to dominate in highly contested, multi-domain
environments and enhance the lethality of the entire Joint Force.

Ultimately, a comprehensive training continuum that combines foundational airmanship with advanced, platform-specific experience
produces a more lethal and adaptable aviator. The program is essential for generating warfighters capable of executing the complex
demands of the National Defense Strategy, ensuring the United States maintains a decisive airpower advantage.

