Description of Strategic Readiness Financed: The Marine Corps’ Operation and Maintenance readiness budget supports the Department’s Strategic Readiness
objectives. Overall readiness decreased due to the right-sizing of surge support within the Consolidated Storage Program and the Defense Property
Accountability System-Warehouse Module, which manage storage, optimization, requisitioning, issuing, repair, and accountability for Class II life cycle
equipment. Additionally, a $0.5 million increase for the Family of Field Medical Equipment to support IT infrastructure supports the sustainment of the Reserve
Force Authorized Medical/Dental Allowance List. This funding supports medical material, data integration, inventory visibility, and readiness tracking across
Marine Reserve medical units., enhancing the readiness of the Service.


