3) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ................................................................................... $37,944
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $3,332,864; FTE Base: 29,522)

4) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................. $92,290
Increased funding and manpower (1,678 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant
to Executive Order 14210, implementing the Presidents Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and
the March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-
validation efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Base Support established requirements.
The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support mission execution and workforce modernization. These FTEs
support mission essential fire, Law Enforcement and emergency services; maintenance and logistics positions; nuclear enterprise
support; Air Operations Centers support for Defense Planning Guidance (DPG) priority investments related to expansion,
modernization, and diversification of our nuclear deterrent and prioritization of the readiness of forces for the Joint Force.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $3,231,146; FTE Base: 29,552; 1,678 FTE)




