5) Operational Communications - Enterprise Information Technology (EIT) Compute & Store ................................................................. $53,710
Funds support Oracle licenses, Enterprise Resource Planning Common Services (ERP-CS), and Cloud One requirements,
addressing historical underfunding of Air Force EIT Compute/Store needs. The Oracle Enterprise Software License Agreement
enables unlimited use of core Oracle products, critical security patches, and expert support for over 300 Department of the Air Force
systems. ERP-CS provides essential cloud infrastructure, cybersecurity, and application support for key DAF ERP systems (e.g.
Defense Enterprise Accounting and Management System (DEAMS); Military Personnel Data System (MILPDS); and Maintenance,
Repair and Overhaul (MRO)), serving as their foundation. Cloud One consolidates critical capabilities into a secure platform,
supporting the Air Force Portal, warfighter applications, AI, data mesh, edge computing, and Zero Trust cybersecurity. This budget
ensures Warfighters have the collaborative software and computing tools needed to sustain a ready and capable force.

OP32:
647 DISA Enterprise Computing Centers
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract

(FY 2026 Base: $2,861,420)

6) Operational Communications - Enterprise Information Technology (EIT) Connect ............................................................................. $157,083
Funds support Defense Information Systems Network (DISN) Infrastructure Services (IS) and Base IT Infrastructure Support
requirements. The increase corrects historical underfunding of EIT Connect requirements. The DISN-IS program is the foundational
service that ensures network connectivity for all daily Department of the Air Force mission. The Base IT Infrastructure Support
program ensures IT infrastructure at DAF locations is sustained and functioning, and replaced as hardware fails, reaches end-of-life,
or is rendered obsolete as technology continues to advance. This budget ensures Warfighters have the secure connectivity and
resilient IT infrastructure to produce a ready and capable force that can meet National Defense Strategy objectives of defending the
homeland and deterring China (and other adversaries).

OP32:
671 DISA DISN Subscription Services
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)
925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $2,861,420)




