                     7) Operational Communications - Enterprise Information Technology (EIT) Enterprise Services............................................................ $259,159
                     Funds support Enterprise IT as a Service (EITaaS), Microsoft 365 and Adobe Enterprise Licenses, Installation Emergency
                     Management, and Unified Capabilities (UC) requirements, addressing historical underfunding of EIT Enterprise Services. EITaaS is
                     the Department of the Air Force's core IT modernization strategy, transitioning bases to a secure, cost-effective, and commercially
                     managed "as-a-service" model. Microsoft 365 provides essential productivity, messaging, and collaboration tools for Airmen and
                     civilians, while the Adobe Enterprise License Agreement delivers 560,000 licenses for secure document creation and management.
                     The UC program replaces outdated analog phone systems with a centralized Voice Over Internet Protocol (VOIP) solution, reducing
                     costs and improving communication security and reliability. This budget ensures Warfighters have the collaborative software, secure
                     IT connectivity, and resilient platforms needed to defend the homeland and deter adversaries.

                     OP32:
