The deployable Air Force ATCALS, in the tactical environment, includes mobile and transportable Airport Surveillance Radar (ASR) and Precision Approach Radar (PAR),
mobile control towers, mobile Tactical Air Navigation systems (TACANs), mobile Very High Frequency Omnidirectional Range (VOR), Very High Frequency Omni-
directional Range Collocated Tactical Air (VORTAC), and the Mobile Microwave Landing System. In the fixed-base environment, which includes both the United States
National Airspace System and support in overseas host nations, ATCALS include fixed airport surveillance and precision approach radars, control towers, TACANs, VORs,
VORTACs, Instrument Landing Systems (ILS) and air traffic control simulators. ATCALS automation and software systems include the Department of War Advanced
Automation System, the Airfield Automation System and the Terminal Instrument Procedures development software tool.




