3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $2,293
Increased funding and manpower (35 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Global C3I & Early Warning Program established
requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support Air Force-wide Strategic Global Command,
Control, Communication, and Intelligence with programs like North Warning System (NWS), North Atlantic Defense System, and the
Integrated Tactical warning and Attack Assessment system.

OP32:101
Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $274,518; FTE Base: 1,892; 35 FTE)



