4) Global Command and Control - Backscatter Radar ............................................................................................................................... $30,000
The increased funding is allocated to sustain and enhance the high-frequency (HF), bistatic ionospheric backscatter radar system,
which is critical for over-the-horizon (OTH) detection and tracking of air and surface targets across vast geographic areas. This
advanced radar technology leverages the ionosphere to extend its range far beyond the line of sight, enabling the monitoring of
activities and threats at distances that traditional radar systems cannot reach. The system provides long-range early detection,
creating valuable decision space and enabling timely responses to potential threats. It will also fund the maintenance and
sustainment of the radar infrastructure, ensuring its reliability and operational readiness.

OP32:
985 Research and Development Contracts

(FY 2026 Base: $780,645)

5) Nuclear Deterrence - Strategic Mission Planning and Execution System (SMPES) ................................................................................ $5,571
Increases sustainment efforts critical Nuclear Command, Control and Communications (NC2/NC3) mission-support capabilities
enabling Combatant Commander of US Strategic Command (CDRUSSTRATCOM) to develop and execute Level 4 nuclear and
conventional war plans, strategic deterrence options, and Global Strike missions. This supports Strategic Mission Planning and
Execution System (SMPES) which integrates six legacy programs into a unified system-of-services delivering nuclear planning,
analysis, and execution support for the CDRUSSTRATCOM.

OP32:
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract

(FY 2026 Base: $137,042)




