                     6) Nuclear Deterrence - Survivable Airborne Operations Center (SAOC) .................................................................................................. $40,700
                     The Sustaining the Nuclear Triad effort is focused on maintaining and modernizing the nation’s strategic nuclear deterrent across its
                     air, land, and sea-based components. A credible deterrent requires an equally survivable Command and Control (C2) system to lead
                     it. Accordingly, this increase funds the critical SAOC and E-4B platform recapitalization. It ensures SAOC and E-4B remain on
                     schedule and preserves the nation’s airborne strategic C2 capability. It further enables transition and bed-down actions, provides
                     critical contract power manpower to reinforce an undermanned organic workforce, and supports security and base upgrades for the
                     new weapon system, strengthening the Air Force’s survivable C2.

