1) Civilian Pay - Average Workyear Cost Adjustment................................................................................................................................. $25,326
Increase in civilian personnel compensation adjusts average workyear costs. Each year, The Air Force uses detailed execution and
cost factor analysis to update civilian compensation costs for the purpose of accurately forecasting budget estimates for the civilian
workforce. The Subactivity Group average cost adjustment is a result of these changes as well as updated pay raise, awards and
benefit assumptions.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $360,027; FTE Base: 2,579)

2) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ..................................................................................... $4,374
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $360,027; FTE Base: 2,579)

3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $6,034
Increased funding and manpower (81 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Other Combat Operations Support Program's
established requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support combat evaluation groups and
strategic missile evaluation squadrons; defensive training; civil engineer heavy repair squadrons (RED HORSE).

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $360,027; FTE Base: 2,579; 81 FTE)




