4) Command and Control Support Activities - Restore Rhombus Guardian............................................................................................... $12,914
Increase supports restoral of configuration of agentic artificial intelligence (AI) capabilities and for Rhombus Guardian, a platform that
provides AI-powered predictive and prescriptive decision support solutions for resources planning and programming. Funding will
improve strategy for budget alignment, advanced data analytics, and strengthen the decision-making capability of our resourcing
workforce. Additionally, the platform strengthens military readiness and lethality by delivering more agile, data-driven, and accurate
planning, programming, budgeting, and execution (PPBE) analysis for decision-makers. The platform independently analyzes data,
identifies issues, and recommends courses of action. This action will enable the AF to leverage advances in AI to optimize and
accelerate resource and readiness decision-making in support of operational and strategic objectives.

OP32:
989 Other Services

(FY 2026 Base: $33,802)

5) Installation Operations and Security - Combat Support Training Ranges .............................................................................................. $69,130
Increase supports efforts to build full operational capability to combat support training ranges, providing realistic environments for
troops to train in critical functions like logistics, engineering, medical support, and base defense. Funding addresses equipment gaps
by acquiring tools, vehicles, and systems to replicate battlefield conditions and improve training realism. This investment ensures
state-of-the-art resources, enhances readiness, strengthens interoperability, and prepares personnel for the demands of modern
warfare.

