Increase addresses a critical staffing shortage for the 16th Air Force cybersecurity mission. Funds provide additional contractor
personnel for Cybersecurity Service Provider (CSSP) Teams for the Nuclear Command, Control, and Communications (NC3) mission
and provides six additional Cyber Operational Readiness Assessment (CORA) teams. Increase also provides for additional travel,
training and Information Technology (IT) equipment requirements commensurate with the increase in personnel. This budget
supports the cybersecurity requirements that defend nuclear and IT systems and infrastructure, which are key to defending the
homeland and deterring adversaries, as per the 2026 National Defense Strategy.

