Increase supports Information Technology (IT) infrastructure by investing in critical asset upgrades, improving end-user experience
and enhancing network performance. Funding will support digital modernization initiatives, cloud transition efforts, and cybersecurity
Zero Trust capabilities, providing secure access to data anytime and from any network. Increase also funds vulnerability
management and IT security support ensuring IT policy-compliant network connectivity for communications across classified and
unclassified networks.

OP32:
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $305,135)

7) Cyberspace Operations - Post-Quantum Crypto Modernization ............................................................................................................ $25,251
Increase for software-based solutions that will protect air-gapped systems, space/satellite assets and cloud environments to ensure
the protection and enhancement of secure communications, Identification Friend or Foe (IFF), Nuclear Command, Control, and
Communications (NC3), and other mission-critical capabilities against adversaries' leaps in quantum computing, which continually
threaten encrypted communications. This budget ensures DAF cybersecurity capabilities remain at the leading edge, prepared and
capable of denying adversaries' access to Air Force and Joint Force critical systems.

OP32:
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)

(FY 2026 Base: $305,135)




                                                                                                                                                       $$, $$89380f5eddf9a2585cdcb579f070991d78cef9556f2f424490a2cff7ef6e784a$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
