                                                                                                       ($ In Thousands)

                     8) Defensive Cyberspace Operations - Information Technology (IT) ......................................................................................................... $14,450
                     This increase is critical for addressing the significant technical debt the Department of the Air Force has accumulated due to deferred
                     investments in IT infrastructure and modernization. This deferment has led to degraded network performance and a diminished user
                     experience, which directly impacts the operational effectiveness of our forces. This efforts are a necessary step to lay the foundation
                     of our transition to a Zero Trust (ZT) security model, consistent with Executive Order 14028 "Improving the Nation's Cyber Security"
                     and National Security Memorandum 8 directing ZT. This increase specifically funds IT services supporting the Department of the Air
                     Force Cyberspace Mission Assurance requirements, ensuring the protection and resilience of Cyber/IT capabilities and infrastructure.
                     The increased funding brings funding into alignment with program requirements.

                     OP32:
                     923 Facility Sustain, Restore Mod By Ct
                     925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

                     (FY 2026 Base: $241,885)

                     9) Defensive Cyberspace Operations - Information Technology (IT) Control Systems ............................................................................ $107,000
                     Increase strengthens cybersecurity infrastructure for IT Control Systems, a critical investment to protect Defense Critical
                     Infrastructure and ensure mission resilience. This funding mitigates vulnerabilities, safeguards homeland defense, and aligns with
                     DAF Enterprise objectives by implementing robust authentication controls and leveraging cost-efficient Commercial Cloud Services.
                     Mission Assurance - Cybersecurity (MA-CS) activities proactively reduce risks, ensure operational continuity, and meet Service
                     responsibilities under DODD 3020.40 and DODI 3020.45. Additionally, this increase supports hardening legacy infrastructure to
                     prevent mission disruptions and protect national security interests

                     OP32:
                     923 Facility Sustain, Restore Mod By Ct

                     (FY 2026 Base: $241,885)


9. Program Decreases .............................................................................................................................................................................................................................. $-88,321

         a) One-Time FY 2026 Costs .................................................................................................................................................................................................. $-1,700




