                     6) Tactical Intelligence and Special Activities - Overseas Operations ........................................................................................................ $19,180
                     Increase supports U.S. Air Forces Central Command (AFCENT) and U.S. Central Command (CENTCOM) at strategic Cooperative
                     Security Locations (CSLs). These CSLs are critical forward-operating sites that enable air operations, Intelligence, Surveillance, and
                     Reconnaissance (ISR) missions, and logistics support in the CENTCOM area of responsibility, which includes the Middle East,
                     Central Asia, and parts of South Asia. Funding will bolster logistics capabilities, ensuring the efficient movement of personnel,
                     supplies, and equipment to and from these strategic locations which will ensure these locations remain fully operational and capable
                     of supporting U.S. and partner nations' objectives in the region. This initiative is vital for maintaining operational readiness, advancing
                     strategic objectives, and ensuring the U.S. and its partners can effectively address evolving challenges in a complex and dynamic
                     security environment.

