                     3) Medical Readiness - Air Force Medical Command (AFMEDCOM) Headquarters .......................................................................................... $0
                     The Air Force stood up the Air Force Medical Command (AFMEDCOM) as a Direct Reporting Unit (DRU) to prioritize DAF Medical
                     and operational readiness, achieve parity with sister services, and continue military authority and accountability in Air Force Medicine.
                     During the transfer of resources from Air Force Medical Readiness Agency, AFMEDCOM developed a strategic resourcing effort to
                     ensure DAF is investing in requirements that prioritize DAF Medical and operational readiness. As a result, DAF is moving $189M
                     from Advisory and Assistance Services to fund Medical Equipment ($43M), Patient Movement ($28M), and Medical Care contracts
                     and services ($118M).

