2) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ..................................................................................... $1,791
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $111,706; FTE Base: 625)

3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $4,680
Increase funding and manpower (52 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Combatant Command Mission Operations -
USNORTHCOM Program established requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support
homeland defense, civil support and security cooperation to defend and secure the US and its interest.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $111,706; FTE Base: 625; 52 FTE)




