4) Direct Mission Support - Advancing Operational Agility and Strategic Readiness ................................................................................. $64,750
Increase funds enable critical operations, activities, and investments for NORAD and USNORTHCOM, addressing emerging priorities
tied to new and expanded missions. These resources strengthen presence activities to demonstrate resolve and support agile force
deployment, while also covering costs for Counter-Small Uncrewed Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS) fly-away kits. Additionally, the funding
facilitates advanced planning for Joint Interagency Task Force-Counter Cartel Headquarters facilities, enhancing the command’s
ability to counter evolving threats and maintain mission readiness.

OP32:
920 Supplies and Materials (Non-DWCF)
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $105,074)

5) Direct Mission Support - Arctic Operations ............................................................................................................................................. $15,826
Increase for Arctic Operations supports the DAF's effort to support multinational operations by funding and increased presence and
operational flexibility activities in the Arctic region. Funds will be used for infrastructure and sustainment to support distributed multi-
domain operations, conduct Arctic area development plans, and complete required environmental assessments for future
construction projects to support expanded operations in the Arctic.

OP32:
920 Supplies and Materials (Non-DWCF)
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

(FY 2026 Base: $105,074)




