3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................. $21,344
Increase funding and manpower (232 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Combatant Command Mission Operations -
USSTRATCOM Program established requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to deter strategic
attack and employ forces to guarantee the security of our nation and allies. The manpower and funding is critical to defending the
homeland and deterring foreign adversaries.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $260,365; FTE Base: 1,264; 232 FTE)

