Increase in funding supports the standardization of Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations (JEMSO) education curriculum and
training, as well as the Joint Center for Electromagnetic Readiness (JCER) acquisition of essential equipment and maintenance to
assess Joint Force EMSO deficiencies, operational risks, and capability requirements, ensuring the effectiveness, survivability, and
interoperability of Joint EMS capabilities.

