                     1) Civilian Pay - Vendor Threat Mitigation ....................................................................................................................................................... $650
                     Increases funding and manpower (4 FTEs) to Vendor Threat Mitigation (VTM). The DoW uses VTM to identify, analyze, and mitigate
                     risk from contractors supporting military operations. This increase focuses on preventing adversaries from accessing critical
                     technology, installations, and funding.

                     OP32:
                     101 Executive General Schedule

                     (FY 2026 Base: $59,358; FTE Base: 315; 4 FTE)

                     2) Civilian Pay - USCENTCOM Operational Contract Support Manpower ................................................................................................... $1,172
                     Transfer increase funding and manpower (8 FTEs) support Operational Contract Support (OCS) ensuring DoW is poised to integrate
