                     3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $3,901
                     Increase funding and manpower (47 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
                     Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
                     March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
                     efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Combatant Command Mission Operations -
                     USCENTCOM Program established requirements. The FY 2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to support security
                     interests in nations stretching from the Arabian gulf region, to Western portions of the Indian Ocean, and into Central Asia.

                     OP32:
                     101 Executive General Schedule

                     (FY 2026 Base: $59,358; FTE Base: 315; 47 FTE)

                     4) Direct Mission Support - Advanced Technology Infrastructure .............................................................................................................. $56,218
                     Increase in funding will enhance the capabilities of OPERATION SHORT CIRCUIT (OSC), a key initiative aimed at countering
                     unmanned systems (UxS) threats before they are deployed. This support will retain essential personnel, provide advanced
                     equipment, and integrate cutting-edge Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (AI/ML) tools for data analysis. Additionally, it will
                     maintain a collaborative workspace for military, civilian, and law enforcement partners to improve coordination and streamline
                     operations. These efforts will expand OSC into a global initiative, leveraging a joint team of technical experts, operators, data
                     scientists, and law enforcement professionals to address unmanned systems threats and their supply chains effectively.

