8. Program Increases .............................................................................................................................................................................................................................. $349,887

         a) Annualization of New FY 2026 Program .................................................................................................................................................................................... $0

         b) One-Time FY 2027 Costs .......................................................................................................................................................................................................... $0

         c) Program Growth in FY 2027 ........................................................................................................................................................................................... $349,887

                     1) Airlift Readiness Account (ARA) ........................................................................................................................................................... $227,760
                     Increase aligns the FY 2027 funding to the most current USTRANSCOM projections for operating expense shortfalls driven by
                     increased costs from the demand for channel missions that exceed revenue collected from the published working capital fund (WCF)
                     rates and the Joint Services' airlift usage. The WCF rates are set to competitive levels with commercial cargo rates. This increase to
                     the ARA budget allows USTRANSCOM to keep the WCF rates at levels comparable to commercial rates and provide timely service
                     to the warfighters across the globe. Lack of funding in this program will increase costs to the Services requiring airlift support, or a
                     reduction in executable flying hours and cargo transport service availability, which increases risks to pilot's mandatory currency rating
                     and delays the delivery time of personnel, equipment and supplies to warfighters.

                     OP32:
                     704 Airlift Readiness Account

                     (FY 2026 Base: $622,096)

                     2) Civilian Pay - Average Workyear Cost Adjustment................................................................................................................................. $20,573
                     Increase in Civilian Personnel compensation adjusts average workyear costs. Each year the Air Force uses detailed execution and
                     cost factor analysis to update civilian compensation costs for the purpose of accurately forecasting budget estimates for the civilian
                     workforce. The Subactivity Group average cost adjustment is a result of these changes as well as updated pay raise, awards and
                     benefit assumptions.

                     OP32:
                     101 Executive General Schedule

                     (FY 2026 Base: $295,148; FTE Base: 2,302)




                                                                                                                                                                                                 $$, $$4b224ceb2510ce61638737195ce055f864291658ca50c8ea0dbf69dfe6cd03fd$$, $$O&M/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Operation & Maintenance Volume I.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
