                                                                         Budget Activity: Mobilization
                                                                Detail by Subactivity Group: Airlift Operations
                                                                               ($ In Thousands)

3) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $4,420
Increase funding and manpower (65 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Airlift Operations Program established requirements.
The FY2027 request reflects the full requirement necessary to enable the movement of people, supplies, and equipment to critical
locations around the world. Additionally, this program provides opportunities for Air Force pilots and aircrews to gain much needed
flight experience which improves readiness.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $295,148; FTE Base: 2,302; 65 FTE)

4) Mobile Aircraft Satellite Communication Connectivity ............................................................................................................................ $28,628
Increase to provide satellite communications connectivity for C-17, KC-135 and KC-46 fleets. These beyond-line-of-site
communications capabilities are lifesaving mitigation measures that provide secure, reliable communications (aircraft-to-control
center and aircraft-to-aircraft), enabling situational awareness and in-flight coordination, in contested airspace. These service
contracts are necessary to ensure in-flight tracking and deconfliction to avoid mishaps and combat losses.

OP32:
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)

(FY 2026 Base: $148,912)

5) Restore Airlift Operations - Transfer from Discretionary to Mandatory................................................................................................... $38,863
Reflects an increase in Airlift Operations funding to restore baseline funding levels after a one-time decrease in FY 2026 due to a
transfer of discretionary funding to be sourced from the Reconciliation Bill (Public Law No: 119-21 - One Big Beautiful Bill Act).

OP32:
707 AMC Training
914 Purchased Communications (Non-DWCF)
922 Equipment Maintenance By Contract
933 Studies, Analysis, and Evaluations

(FY 2026 Base: $648,524)



