                     6) Senior Leader Communications System ................................................................................................................................................ $29,643
                     Increase to provide senior leader Command, Control and Communication (C3) capabilities to the nation's senior leaders (e.g.
                     President, Vice President, Secretary of War, Secretary of State, Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, Combatant Commanders, etc.)
                     while airborne. This budget represents a focus on peace through strength and defense of the homeland by providing secure, reliable
                     communications, constantly while senior leaders are in-transit across the country and around the world, ensuring their ability to
                     maintain situational awareness of information and events in real-time. These C3 capabilities cannot be met by strictly traditional
                     means (e.g. radio) that are vulnerable to modern threats, but through resilient space-based connectivity. The stability of the
                     communications capabilities aboard these aircraft [two VC-25A; four C32A; four C-40B; seven C-40C; sixteen C-37; two Roll-On
                     Conference Capsules/Steel Eagles] directly affects their readiness and availability for the kill chain, and all war-time mission
                     requirements.

                     OP32:
                     671 DISA DISN Subscription Services

                     (FY 2026 Base: $221,041)



