                     Decrease to Airlift Support (O&M) funds aligns programming to anticipated operational tempo for contingency training flying
                     hours. The projected volume of flight operations in-theater directly impacts the aircraft availability and cumulative flying hours required
                     for pilots to meet training requirements. This program provides the highest quality time for aircrews in C-5 and C-17 airframes to
                     maintain war-time proficiency for near peer conflicts, separate from their highly monetized flying to deliver cargo for USTRANSOM
                     mission.

