                     1) Sustainment of Regional Base Cluster Positioning ................................................................................................................................ $20,000
                     The Campaigning in the Indo-Pacific effort is centered on enhancing force posture, operational capabilities, and partner integration to
                     deter aggression in the Indo-Pacific region. Enhancing this force posture requires the precise alignment of resources to the point of
                     need. Therefore, this action transfers funds to Mobilization Preparedness (Subactivity Group 21D, $20,000) from Other Combat
                     Operations Support Programs (Subactivity Group 12C, -$20,000) to support increased requirements for Pacific Air Forces (PACAF)
                     Regional Base Clustering Positioning asset sustainment. This supports integrated campaigning and enables the Joint Force to
                     conduct global airfield operations to achieve military strategic objectives in contested environments.

                     OP32:
                     925 Equipment Purchases (Non-Fund)

                     (FY 2026 Base: $235,103)

                     2) Nuclear Deterrence Operations ................................................................................................................................................................ $7,800
                     Increase reflects a transfer of funds to Depot Purchase Equipment Maintenance (Subactivity 11M +$11,100), Global C3I and Early
                     Warning (Subactivity 12A +$17,400), Other Combat Operations Support Programs (Subactivity 12C +$7,600), Mobilization
                     Preparedness (Subactivity 21D +$7,800), Other Servicewide Activities (Subactivity 42G +$2,000), and Research, Development,
                     Test, and Evaluation (RDT&E), Air Force (+$7,100) from Combatant Command Mission Operations - USSTRATCOM (Subactivity
                     15D -$53,000) in support of Nuclear Deterrence Operations high-priority items within the nuclear portfolio in order to optimize
                     resource allocation and ensure long-term sustainability of nuclear deterrent capabilities.

