                                                      Detail by Subactivity Group: Officer Acquisition
                                                                      ($ In Thousands)

2) Active Duty Military End Strength Growth - United States Air Force Academy (USAFA) ........................................................................ $5,600
Increase funds to support the active duty military end strength growth. The increased funding will cover the operation and
maintenance costs to support the Cadet Wing and Preparatory School's Mitchell Hall food services contract, Dean of Faculty
equipment purchases, and Information Technology Services to support data processing and network operations. The lack of
resources will reduce the capacity to meet the increased officer accession throughput and reduce potential interest from future cadets
considering attendance at a Service Academy. This increase is the first of a multi-year investment to support active duty end strength
growth.

OP32:
914 Purchased Communications (Non-Fund)
922 Equipment Maintenance by Contract
964 Other Cost (Subsistence and Support of Persons)

(FY 2026 Base: $127,751)

3) Civilian Pay - Enhanced Performance Award Pool for DoW Civilian Employees ..................................................................................... $1,520
Increased funding strengthens the Department's ability to recognize and reward the civilian workforce whose expertise and continuity
underpin mission success. Expanded award capacity helps retain the talent that sustains warfighter readiness, drives innovation, and
ensures uninterrupted support across the enterprise. Investing in civilian recognition directly reinforces the workforce that delivers
stability, operation excellence, and long-term capability for the Department.

OP32:
101 Executive General Schedule

(FY 2026 Base: $116,797; FTE Base: 783)




