                     4) Civilian Pay - Workforce Modernization .................................................................................................................................................... $9,953
                     Increase funding and manpower (88 FTEs) reflects the alignment of civilian staffing to validated mission requirements pursuant to
                     Executive Order 14210, implementing the President’s Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative and the
                     March 2025 Deputy Secretary of War memorandum. The Air Force conducted comprehensive data-hygiene and manpower-validation
                     efforts, resulting in a correction where FY2026 staffing levels were set below the Officer Acquisition Program established
                     requirements, resulting in a suppressed baseline, which produces a larger year-over-year variance. The FY 2027 request reflects the
                     full requirement necessary to support the U.S. Air Force Academy and Officer Training School.

                     OP32:
                     101 Executive General Schedule

                     (FY 2026 Base: $116,797; FTE Base: 783; 88 FTE)

                     5) United States Air Force Academy (USAFA) - Warfighter Initiative ......................................................................................................... $25,000
                     Increases funds for the USAFA Warfighter Initiative effort, enhancing USAFA's commitment to future leader's Warfighter
                     Development. This investment expands on the comprehensive Warfighter Training at USAFA and is required to support the
                     warfighter. The increased funding will buy equipment storage, field operations sustainment gear, and logistics and mobility support to
                     enable movement of equipment across training areas.

                     OP32:
                     935 Training and Leadership Development

                     (FY 2026 Base: $127,751)


